[size=4][u]Station Production Overview[/u][/size]

Adds a [b]Production Overview[/b] tab to the info panel tab strip in the map menu (alongside Object Info, Crew, etc.) for player-owned stations. Shows per-ware production and consumption rates, groups wares into Products, Intermediates, and Resources, and previews the impact of planned (not yet built) modules.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Production Overview Tab[/b]: A dedicated tab in the station info panel shows all production and consumption data at a glance.
[*] [b]Sector Production Overview[/b]: A dedicated tab in the sector info panel shows all production stations within the sector with their respective production data, equal to the single station production overview.
[*] [b]Per-ware rates[/b]: For each ware the tab displays produced, consumed, and net total amounts per hour.
[*] [b]Ware icons[/b]: Each ware row shows the ware icon alongside its name for quick visual identification.
[*] [b]Production issue indicators[/b]: If any production modules for a ware are waiting for resources or waiting for storage, the ware name is highlighted in warning colour and a mouseover tooltip lists the exact issue counts per state.
[*] [b]Live vs Estimated mode[/b]: A dropdown lets you switch between [i]Current (live state)[/i] (reflecting only active modules and workforce) and [i]Estimated (all modules active)[/i] (the theoretical maximum output).
[*] [b]Active module count[/b]: In live mode the module count column shows how many modules are currently running out of the total installed (e.g. [b]3 (5)[/b]).
[*] [b]Ware grouping[/b]: Wares are grouped into [b]Products[/b] (not consumed on-site), [b]Intermediates[/b] (produced and consumed on-site), and [b]Resources[/b] (pure inputs, not produced on-site).
[*] [b]Workforce resource consumption[/b]: Wares consumed exclusively by workforce (food, medicine, and similar consumer goods) appear in the Resources group when no production module produces them. Otherwise they are shown according to their production modules places.
[*] [b]Planned module preview[/b]: When the construction plan contains new modules a second delta row per ware shows the expected impact once those modules are built.
[*] [b]Empire balance[/b]: For Products and Intermediates, an optional [i]All stations:[/i] sub-row shows the total consumption of that ware across all your player-owned stations and a coloured balance indicating how much this station's production covers the empire-wide demand. Hidden by default; enable it with the [b]Show empire balance[/b] checkbox below the mode dropdown. Respects the current Live / Estimated mode.
[*] [b]Configurable data refresh[/b]: A slider in the Extensions options menu (Extensions > Station Production Overview) controls how many UI ticks production data is cached before recomputing (1-10, default 3), reducing CPU overhead in large saves.
[*] [b]Quick-navigation buttons[/b]: [i]Configure Station[/i] and [i]Station Overview[/i] buttons are available at the bottom of the tab.
[/list]
