[size=3][u][b]Usage[/b][/u][/size]

Open the map, select a player-owned station, and click the [b]Production Overview[/b] tab in the info panel on the left or right side.

[size=3][u][i]Production Overview Tab[/i][/u][/size]

The tab renders a table with one row per ware that is produced or consumed by the station's production and processing modules.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/production_overview_tab.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Live vs Estimated mode[/i][/u][/size]

Use the dropdown at the top of the tab to switch between two display modes:

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/production_calculation_type_dropdown.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]Current (live state) / hour[/b]: uses the actual running rate from the engine, accounting for modules that are idle due to missing resources or workforce shortages. The Modules column shows [b]active (total)[/b] when not all modules are running.
[*] [b]Estimated (all modules active) / hour[/b]: reports the theoretical rate assuming all installed modules run at full capacity with the current workforce bonus applied.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/production_estimated.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Planned module preview[/i][/u][/size]

If the station's construction plan contains new production or processing modules that have not been built yet, a secondary delta row appears directly below the ware row. It shows:
[list]
[*] [b](+N)[/b] in the Modules column: the number of planned new modules
[*] The additional production/consumption contribution those modules would add once built
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Ware groups[/i][/u][/size]

Wares are organized into three groups:
[list]
[*] [b]Products[/b]: wares produced at this station that are not also consumed as a resource by any other module here.
[*] [b]Intermediates[/b]: wares that are both produced and consumed internally (e.g. a station that refines ore into silicon and then uses that silicon further).
[*] [b]Resources[/b]: wares consumed as raw inputs that are not produced on-site.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Workforce resource consumption[/i][/u][/size]

Wares that are consumed exclusively by workforce modules (e.g. food, medicine, and similar consumer goods) are shown in the Resources group when no production module produces them.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/workforce_resource_usage.png[/img]

If there are production modules for those wares, they are shown according to their production modules places, and the workforce consumption is shown in the consumption column for that ware.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/workforce_resource_production.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Empire balance[/i][/u][/size]

Below the mode dropdown (single-station view only) a [b]Show empire balance[/b] checkbox controls whether an extra [i]All stations:[/i] sub-row is shown for each Product and Intermediate ware. When enabled, the sub-row displays:
[list]
[*] empire-wide production of that ware across all player-owned stations
[*] empire-wide consumption of that ware across all player-owned stations
[*] a coloured [b]balance[/b] (green = surplus, red = deficit, grey = neutral)
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/show_empire_balance.png[/img]

The balance respects the current Live / Estimated mode. The checkbox is hidden in Sector view.

[size=3][u][i]Extensions options[/i][/u][/size]

Open [b]Extension options > Station Production Overview[/b] in the game [b]Options Menu[/b] to configure:
[list]
[*] [b]Data Refresh Interval[/b]: how many UI ticks the cached production data is reused before a full recompute (1-10, default 3). Lower values give more up-to-date numbers; higher values reduce CPU usage.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/options.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Sector Production Overview[/i][/u][/size]

When viewing the info panel for a sector, a similar [b]Production Overview[/b] tab lists all player-owned production stations in that sector with their respective production data, equal to the single station production overview.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationProductionOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/sector_production_overview_tab.png[/img]

